{{Infobox person | name = La Veneno | birth_name = José Antonio Ortiz Rodríguez | other_names = Cristina Ortiz Rodríguez | birth_date = {{birth date|1964|03|19}} | birth_place = [[Adra, Almería]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2016|11|09|1964|03|19}} | death_place = [[Madrid]], [[Spain]] | death_cause = [[Traumatic brain injury]] after [[accidental fall]] | occupation = [[Vedette (cabaret)|Vedette]], [[singer]] and [[actress]] | years_active = 1996-2016 }}
'''Cristina Ortiz Rodríguez''' (19 March 1964 – 9 November 2016), better known as '''La Veneno''' ("Poison"), was a Spanish [[transsexual]] [[vedette (cabaret)|vedette]], [[singer]] and actress. She is better known for appearing in the [[late-night talk show]]s ''Esta noche cruzamos el Mississippi'' and ''La sonrisa del pelícano'', broadcast between 1996–97 and hosted by journalist Pepe Navarro.
==Biography== La Veneno was born José Antonio Ortiz Rodríguez in [[Adra, Spain|Adra]], [[Province of Almería|Almería]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telecinco.es/salvame/2016/noviembre/11-11-16/Adra-infancia-Veneno-Joselito-conocida_2_2274330139.html |title=Los vecinos de Adra hablan de la infancia de La Veneno, Joselito, como era allí conocida |last=León |first=José Antonio |date=11 November 2016 |access-date=4 August 2018 |work=[[Telecinco]] |publisher=[[Mediaset España]] |language=es}}</ref> the daughter of José María Ortiz López and María Jesús Rodríguez Rivera.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telecinco.es/salvame/2016/noviembre/10-11-16/vida-Cristina-Veneno-conocida-Joselito_2_2273805125.html |title=Así fue la vida de Cristina La Veneno, antes conocida como Joselito |date=10 November 2016 |access-date=4 August 2018 |work=[[Telecinco]] |publisher=[[Mediaset España]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telecinco.es/salvame/2016/noviembre/11-11-16/Familiar-Veneno-siempre-frivola-homofoba_2_2274330143.html |title=Familiar de La Veneno: "Su madre ha sido siempre muy frívola y homófoba..." |date=11 November 2016 |access-date=4 August 2018 |work=[[Telecinco]] |publisher=[[Mediaset España]]}}</ref> She noted from an early age that she was different from other children and as such was never accepted in her village.<ref name="Interviu">{{Cite journal |title=La Veneno pasa factura |url=http://www.interviu.es/reportajes/articulos/la-veneno-pasa-factura |date=24 April 2006 |access-date=9 November 2016 |magazine=[[Interviu]] |language=es |last=Montero |first=Daniel |publisher=Grupo Zeta}}</ref>
In 1991 she went to Madrid. Later she started her process of transition and worked as prostitute in [[Parque del Oeste]] park in Madrid. There she was discovered in 1996 by journalist and TV host Pepe Navarro, who cast her for numerous collaborations in his late nights ''Esta noche cruzamos el Mississippi'' and ''La sonrisa del pelícano''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elmundo.es/papel/2007/06/11/comunicacion/2137294.html |title=Ningún espacio seduce masivamente a la gran audiencia trasnochadora |newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]] |date=11 June 2007 |access-date=4 August 2018 |publisher=Mundinteractivos, [[Sociedad Anónima|S.A.]] |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20071227164859/http://www.elmundo.es/papel/2007/06/11/comunicacion/2137294.html |archive-date=27 December 2007 |language=es |last=Fernández |first=Ángel |location=Madrid}}</ref>
From 2003-06, she served prison time for arson and insurance fraud.<ref name="Interviu"/> In 2006, weighing 122 kilos and showing physical deterioration she reappeared in gossip TV shows.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-21-04-2006/abc/Nacional/prisiones-denuncia-a-la-veneno-por-decir-que-sufrio-abusos-en-la-carcel_1421227750982.html |title=Prisiones denuncia a "La Veneno" por decir que sufrió abusos en la cárcel |newspaper=[[ABC (Spain)|ABC]] |date=21 April 2006 |access-date=4 August 2018 |language=es |location=Madrid}}</ref>
From 2010-12 she suffered from bulimia and depression. In addition, her boyfriend disappeared with her savings (more than 60&nbsp;000 euros) and so she was left with a house and a pension of 300 euros.<ref>{{Cite news |title=La Veneno, perdida por los hombres de mal vivir |url=http://www.elmundo.es/loc/2016/11/12/5825fa08468aeb593a8b4668.html |date=12 November 2016 |access-date=12 November 2016 |newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]] |language=es |last=Diéguez |first=Antonio |publisher=[[Unidad Editorial]]}}</ref>
On 3 October 2016, she launched her long awaited memoir book, ''Digo! Ni puta ni Santa. Las memorias de La Veneno'', co-written with the help of her friend Valeria Vegas.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.libertaddigital.com/chic/entretenimiento/2016-10-10/la-veneno-desvela-en-sus-memorias-sus-relaciones-con-politicos-y-futbolistas-1276584078/ |title='La Veneno' desvela en sus memorias sus relaciones con políticos y futbolistas |author=J. B. L. |date=10 October 2016 |access-date=4 August 2018 |newspaper=[[Libertad Digital]] |language=es}}</ref>
On 5 November 2016, she was found in her house with bruises and suffering from [[traumatic brain injury]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abc.es/estilo/gente/abci-veneno-coma-ajuste-cuentas-201611072003_noticia.html |title="La Veneno", en coma tras ser hallada con un golpe en la cabeza y numerosas contusiones |location=Madrid |date=7 November 2016 |access-date=12 November 2016 |newspaper=[[Diario ABC]] |language=es |quote=Creen que las declaraciones de la actriz, donde afirmó que había estado con hombres muy poderosos del país pudo provocar algún tipo de venganza. Al parecer, había recibido varias amenazas acerca de unas informaciones que tenía pensado dar en exclusiva en su próxima aparición televisiva.}}</ref> She was found by her boyfriend lying on the sofa.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://elpais.com/ccaa/2016/11/07/madrid/1478533840_647495.html |title=La Veneno, ingresada en coma en el hospital La Paz |last=Barroso |first=Francisco Javier |location=Madrid |date=7 November 2016 |access-date=4 August 2018 |newspaper=[[El País]] |language=es |publisher=Prisa}}</ref> She was transferred to the [[Hospital Universitario La Paz]], where she died on 9 November 2016.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Muere La Veneno |url=http://www.elmundo.es/loc/2016/11/09/582302edca4741a4318b46b0.html |access-date=12 November 2016 |newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]] |language=es |date=9 November 2016 |last=F. Durán |first=Luis |publisher=[[Unidad Editorial]]}}</ref> The autopsy determined that the cause of death was an accidental fall.<ref>{{Cite news |title=La autopsia confirma que La Veneno murió por una caída accidental |url=http://www.larazon.es/lifestyle/gente/muere-la-veneno-en-coma-desde-el-sabado-tras-sufrir-un-fuerte-golpe-en-la-cabeza-FL13903125 |date=13 November 2016 |access-date=27 March 2018 |newspaper=[[La Razón (Madrid)|La Razón]] |language=es |last=Bayón |first=Ángel}}</ref>
While she was hospitalized on [[Intensive care unit|ICU]],<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.lecturas.com/actualidad/muere-la-veneno-tras-llevar-dias-coma_23120 |title=Muere ‘La Veneno’, tras estar 4 días en coma |date=9 November 2016 |access-date=11 November 2016 |magazine=Lecturas |language=es}}</ref> close people to La Veneno speculated that the cause of death was a settle of scores,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vanitatis.elconfidencial.com/noticias/2016-11-07/la-veneno-coma-uci-hospital-la-paz-paliza-ajuste-de-cuentas_1286285/ |title=La Veneno, en coma tras recibir una paliza por un "ajuste de cuentas" |last=Higuera |first=Raoul |date=7 November 2016 |access-date=11 November 2016 |newspaper=[[El Confidencial]] |language=es |publisher=Titania Compañía Editorial, [[Sociedad Limitada|S.L.]]}}</ref> because she received [[death threat]]s after the publication of her autobiography.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/gente/20161009/41882327209/la-veneno-libro-memorias.html |title=La Veneno: "Me he acostado con gente que con un dedo mueve España" |last=Guerra |first=Andrés |date=10 October 2016 |access-date=11 November 2016 |newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]] |language=es}}</ref>
