{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}} {{Use British English|date=May 2015}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Vincent Blore | image = | fullname = | height = | birth_date = {{Birth date |1907|2|25|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Uttoxeter]], England | death_date = 1997 | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | years1 = | clubs1 = Uttoxeter Amateurs | years2 = {{0|000}}?–1932 | clubs2 = [[Burton Town F.C.|Burton Town]] | years3 = 1932–1933 | clubs3 = [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 1933–35 | clubs4 = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] | caps4 = 15 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 1935–36 | clubs5 = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] | caps5 = 9 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 1936–38 | clubs6 = [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] | caps6 = 33 | goals6 = 0 | years7 = 1938–{{0|000}}? | clubs7 = [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]] | caps7 = | goals7 =
}} '''Vincent P. Blore''' (25 February 1907 – 1997)<ref name="whustats">{{cite web | url=http://www.westhamstats.info/westham.php?west=2&ham=62&united=Vincent_Blore| title=Welcome to the Wonderful World of West Ham United Statistics&nbsp;— Vincent Blore | publisher=www.westhamstats.info | accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref> also known as '''Vince Blore''' was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Uttoxeter Amateurs, [[Burton Town F.C.|Burton Town]], [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]], [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] and [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]].
==Footballing career== Blore played for Uttoxeter Amateurs, [[Burton Town F.C.|Burton Town]] and Aston Villa before moving to Derby County in August 1933.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.astonvillaplayerdatabase.com/134.html | title=Blore, Vincent P. "Vic" | publisher=www.astonvillaplayerdatabase.com | accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref> He made his debut for Derby on 19 August 1934 in a 2-0 away defeat to [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.11v11.com/matches/leicester-city-v-derby-county-19-april-1934-67274/ | title=Leicester City v Derby County 19 April 1934 | publisher=www.11v11.com | accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref> Blore made only 15 appearances before moving to West Ham in 1935. Known as "Vic" by [[West Ham United F.C. supporters|West Ham fans]], he was signed by manager, [[Charlie Paynter]]. His debut came on 31 August 1935 in a 4-3 away defeat to [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref name=whustats/> 'Keeper [[Herman Conway]] arrived later that season making Blore second-choice and with the arrival of [[Arthur Weare|Jack Weare]] from [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] he became third choice 'keeper. In 1936 Crystal Palace offered him regular first team football. He played for Palace until October 1938 when he signed for [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://theyflysohigh.co.uk/charlie-paynter/4545965284 | title=Charlie Paynter | publisher=Theyflysohigh | accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.holmesdale.net/page.php?id=319&yearfrom=1938 | title=Transfers - 1938/39 | publisher=www.holmsdate.net | accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref>
